{"word":"θνητός","slug":"θνητός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θνητός</b></el> <el>(θνητός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:θνήσκω'><el>θνήσκω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>liable to death, mortal</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <el>θνητοί</el> <i>mortals</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <i>befitting mortals, human</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}